[ ] WS3-06 AVX2 optimized Q4_0 dot product (inline asm)\n72:- [ ] WS3-07 AVX2 optimized Q8_0 dot product (inline asm)\n73:- [ ] WS3-08 Benchmark: Q4_0 dot product ops/sec (naive vs AVX2)\n75:### WS4 — Matrix Operations\n76:- [ ] WS4-01 Implement naive matmul (quantized input, integer accumulator)\n77:- [ ] WS4-02 Implement row-major / col-major layout handling\n78:- [ ] WS4-03 AVX2 tiled matmul (cache-friendly blocking)\n79:- [ ] WS4-04 Implement element-wise operations (add, mul, scale)\n80:- [ ] WS4-05 Benchmark: matmul GOPS for typical LLM dimensions (4096x4096)\n82:### WS5 — LLaMA Forward Pass\n83:- [ ] WS5-01 Implement RoPE (Rotary Position Embedding) in integer math\n84:- [ ] WS5-02 Implement GQA (Grouped Query Attention) — Q/K/V projection, score, softmax, output\n85:- [ ] WS5-03 Implement SwiGLU FFN (gate * up projection, silu activation, down projection)\n86:- [ ] WS5-04 Implement transformer block (attention + FFN + residual + RMSNorm)\n87:- [ ] WS5-05 Implement full forward pass (embed -> N blocks -> final norm -> logits)\n88:- [ ] WS5-06 Implement KV cache for autoregressive generation\n89:- [ ] WS5-07 Validation: compare logits against llama.cpp for first token of known prompt\n91:### WS6 — Tokenizer\n92:- [ ] WS6-01 Implement BPE vocabulary loader from GGUF metadata\n93:- [ ] WS6-02 Implement BPE encode (text -> token IDs)\n94:- [ ] WS6-03 Implement BPE decode (token IDs -> text)\n95:- [ ] WS6-04 Handle special tokens (BOS, EOS, padding)\n96:- [ ] WS6-05 Validation: tokenize/detokenize round-trip matches llama.cpp\n98:### WS7 — Sampling & Generation\n99:- [ ] WS7-01 Implement temperature scaling on logits\n100:- [ ] WS7-02 Implement top-k sampling\n101:- [ ] WS7-03 Implement top-p (nucleus) sampling\n102:- [ ] WS7-04 Implement repetition penalty\n103:- [ ] WS7-05 Implement autoregressive generation loop (prompt -> tokens one at a time)\n104:- [ ] WS7-06 Implement `Inference(prompt, max_tokens, temp, top_k, top_p);` HolyC API\n106:### WS8 — Integration 